title: High Social Contributions
description: In 2022, social contributions accounted for 56.03% of Germany's total revenue, indicating a strong social security system.

title: Long Duration of Secondary Education
description: Germany offers a comprehensive secondary education lasting 9 years, as of 2023, providing a robust foundation for higher education and vocational training.

title: Low Prevalence of Underweight in Young Females
description: In 2016, only 0.2% of German girls under 5 were underweight, reflecting effective child nutrition programs.

title: Low Prevalence of Overweight in Young Males
description: As of 2016, just 0.7% of German boys under 5 were overweight, showcasing successful health and nutrition strategies.

title: Minimal Stunting in Young Males
description: In 2016, only 0.4% of boys under 5 in Germany experienced stunting, indicating effective early childhood health interventions.

title: Negative Net Capital Account Balance
description: Germany's net capital account balance was -$28.71 billion in 2023, suggesting more capital outflows than inflows.
